{"metadata": {"synopsis": "Col. Terry Childers (Samuel L. Jackson) is a 30-year Marine veteran: a decorated officer with combat experience in Vietnam, Beirut and Desert Storm -- a patriot, a hero. But now, the country he served so well has put him on trial for a rescue mission that went terribly wrong. For his attorney, he has chosen Marine Col. Hays Hodges (Tommy Lee Jones), a comrade-in-arms who owes his life to Childers.", "rating": "36", "genre": "Action & Adventure/Drama/Mystery & Suspense", "runtime": "2h 8m", "director": "William Friedkin", "studio": "ParamountPictures,SevenArtsPictures,RoeProductionsKG", "theater_date": "Mar 31, 2000", "dvd_date": "Aug 1, 2013", "box_office": "$61.3M"}, "reviews": {"reviews": ["The drama effectively combines combat and potboiler courtroom drama.", "Tense but shallow military drama heavy on violence, language", "Something is missing", "If the makers hadn't stuck so closely to the rules, this film would have been far more engaging.", "", "", "", "", "Not exactly a triumphant return to form for maverick director William Friedkin, but it's not bad, either.", "", "", "", "", "Whereas a TV version of the same material might flounder, this slick, big-budget film works because there is legitimate doubt as to both the level of guilt of the accused and the outcome of the trial.", "", "A thriller set in Yemen that turns into an ethical examination of the use of force by the military.", "", "", "", ""], "rating": ["B-", "2/5", "C", "2/4", "3/5", "2.5/4", "2/5", "2/5", "3/4", "2/4", "4/5", "2/5", "2/5", "2.5/4", "2/5", "", "D", "2.5/4", "1/4", "5/10"], "fresh": ["fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "fresh", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten", "rotten"], "critic": ["Dennis Schwartz", "Andrea Beach", "John A. Nesbit", "Michael Dequina", "Mark Halverson", "Joe Lozito", "", "", "Jeffrey M. Anderson", "Jeanne Aufmuth", "John R. McEwen", "", "